    Bank manipulation

    Create, Update, Find Bank return @void

    Example request:

    curl -X GET "http://classy.pos/Api/V1/Banks/Bank/List" \
-H "Accept: application/json"
    var settings = {
    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://classy.pos/Api/V1/Banks/Bank/List",
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

-H "Accept: application/json"

    HTTP Request

    GET Api/V1/Banks/Bank/Filter/{ID}/{Name}/{IsDefault}/{Status}/{FromDate}/{ToDate}

    HEAD Api/V1/Banks/Bank/Filter/{ID}/{Name}/{IsDefault}/{Status}/{FromDate}/{ToDate}

    Contact manipulation

    Create, Update, Find Contact return @void

    Example request:

    curl -X GET "http://classy.pos/Api/V1/Contacts/Contact/List" \
-H "Accept: application/json"

    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://classy.pos/Api/V1/Contacts/Contact/List",

        "accept": "application/json"

}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

    curl -X GET "http://classy.pos/Api/V1/Contacts/Contact/Details/{ContactID}" \
-H "Accept: application/json"

    "async": true,

    HTTP Request

    GET Api/V1/Accounts/Expense/Filter/{ID}/{Phone}/{Email}/{Status}/{FromDate}/{ToDate}

    HEAD Api/V1/Accounts/Expense/Filter/{ID}/{Phone}/{Email}/{Status}/{FromDate}/{ToDate}

    ExpenseCategory manipulation

    Create, Update, Find ExpenseCategory return @void

    Example request:

    curl -X GET "http://classy.pos/Api/V1/Accounts/Expense/Category/List" \
-H "Accept: application/json"

    GET Api/V1/Accounts/Income/Filter/{ID}/{Phone}/{Email}/{Status}/{FromDate}/{ToDate}

    HEAD Api/V1/Accounts/Income/Filter/{ID}/{Phone}/{Email}/{Status}/{FromDate}/{ToDate}

    IncomeCategory manipulation

    Create, Update, Find IncomeCategory return @void

    Example request:

-H "Accept: application/json"

    Create, Update, Find Product return @void

-H "Accept: application/json"

    "async": true,

    HTTP Request

    GET Api/V1/Products/Product/Ledger/{CategoryID}/{ContactID}/{FromDate}/{ToDate}

    HEAD Api/V1/Products/Product/Ledger/{CategoryID}/{ContactID}/{FromDate}/{ToDate}

    Api/V1/Products/Product/Ledger/Filter/{ProductID}/{PurchaseID}/{WarehouseID}/{RackID}/{BatchNo}/{Status}/{FromDate}/{ToDate}

    Example request:

    curl -X GET "http://classy.pos/Api/V1/Products/Product/Ledger/Filter/{ProductID}/{PurchaseID}/{WarehouseID}/{RackID}/{BatchNo}/{Status}/{FromDate}/{ToDate}" \
-H "Accept: application/json"
    var settings = {
    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://classy.pos/Api/V1/Products/Product/Ledger/Filter/{ProductID}/{PurchaseID}/{WarehouseID}/{RackID}/{BatchNo}/{Status}/{FromDate}/{ToDate}",
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

-H "Accept: application/json"

    "async": true,
